GIT Notes - 
----------------------------
Distributed Version Control System - Can create local repos, commit changes into local repo. Can merge/pull the changes into the master by
raising a pull request.

Commands
 >> git add ----> create a local git repo
 >> git status -----> Status
 >> git commit -----> submit changes to the file in local repositry
 >> git log  ---> Submit / change history
 >> git diff HEAD~1..HEAD --> HEAD is the latest commit to the repositry. 
      ~n n versions back from the HEAD
 >> git add prepares files for commit, it's called staging area.
 >> rm file.txt ---> git add -u -----> git commit --> removes file from repo
 >> mv file1.txt file2.txt ---> git add -A ----> renames file after commit
 >> git reset --hard ----> change the work copy to that of the head
 >> git checkout file-name ----> revert the changes that aren;'t necessary, reverts to the HEAD
 >> git reset soft --> adds HEAD to the staging area
 >> git reset --hard HEAD~1
 >> Git ignore - ignoring files like logs etc
     Add a file called .gitgnore to the root directoty and inside list all the files to ignore.
 
